Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join to sharp turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with symbol and Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 80, 22? Name Ainos. This appears to be a new variant.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0901)
